Text:
Brave isn‚Äôt winning right now.

Brave doesn‚Äôt spread hate or bully the vulnerable. 
Brave doesn‚Äôt put greed and self-interest over millions of lives. 
Brave doesn‚Äôt cower behind lies and walls. 
Brave doesn‚Äôt pit people against one another. That‚Äôs what fear does.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
President Trump is tearing apart the moral fabric of this country. He demonizes the vulnerable and he punches down. He puts his name in bold on every building.

He does all of this because he wants us to believe he is strong. He is not. Our President is a coward.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
We deserve a president who is brave. A president who inspires us to stand for something greater than ourselves.

We don‚Äôt build walls; we build bridges. Because our unity of purpose lifts us higher than any tower.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
Day in and day out, Americans are making a choice to resist the backward pull of this administration, and pushing us toward a better future.

The people of this country deserve a president worthy of your bravery. That's why I‚Äôm running for president.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
My grandmother Polly taught me that being brave doesn‚Äôt just mean standing up for yourself‚Äîit means standing up for other people who need you. 

Bravery means standing up to the powerful, and summoning the courage to confront them head on. And that's what I've done.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
I stood up to greed and voted against the bank bailout.

I stood up to corruption in Congress.

I stood up to the Pentagon, Congress and colleges on behalf of survivors of sexual assault.
 
And I‚Äôm proud to have stood up to Trump more than anyone else in the Senate.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
I‚Äôm fighting for an America where where compassion and integrity define our government, not self-interest and corruption. Where we don‚Äôt just care about the profits we make today, but the future we‚Äôre leaving to our grandchildren.

I know we can be that America.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
Right now, special interests are displacing the voices of the people in our democracy. Find me a so-called unsolvable problem, and I'll point you to the greed and corruption in the way.

We need to crack open our government, flip the switch and let the light flood in.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
As president, I will fight for publicly-funded federal elections. It would change the way Washington works overnight. Imagine your voice being just as loud as the Koch brothers‚Äîwhat a concept!

We have to level the political playing field so our democracy can thrive.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
Our goals are ambitious, but they shouldn't be controversial:

Medicare for all.
Universal pre-K and high-quality public education.
Affordable college.
Full employment.
A $15 minimum wage.
National paid leave.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
Hear me when I say this: Paid leave, equal pay and affordable daycare are not just ‚Äúwomen‚Äôs issues.‚Äù These are economic issues‚Äîones that will determine whether or not our country succeeds. 

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
We need to dismantle institutional racism.
 
We need solutions both targeted and broad‚Äîlike higher standards for maternity care, a national commitment to full employment, postal banking, ending cash bail and legalizing marijuana.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
We need to restore our moral leadership in the world. We must secure our borders effectively and fight terrorism relentlessly, but let‚Äôs be very clear: Racism and fear are not a national security strategy.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
We must hold accountable any threats to our democracy.

The Mueller report must be made public. Nobody is above the law. I don‚Äôt often agree with Richard Nixon, but he was right to say the American people have a right to know whether or not their president is a crook.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
We need to treat climate change like the existential threat it is and pass a #GreenNewDeal. Let‚Äôs make it our generation‚Äôs moonshot. Addressing a global challenge of this urgency will take massive effort and transformative vision‚Äîwhich is exactly why we should do it.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:
None of these big fights will be easy. But I‚Äôve never backed down from a fight for what‚Äôs right, and I‚Äôm not about to start now.

That‚Äôs why I‚Äôm in this race. I'm running for president to fix what‚Äôs been broken, repair our moral fabric and rebuild our common bonds.

#BraveWins
Name: Kirsten Gillibrand

Text:

We stood up, locked arms and proved to America‚Äîand the world‚Äîthat when people come together to drive out darkness, hope rises.

Fear loses.

And #BraveWins.
